import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, label='Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wages', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['wages'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of wages?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Wages")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    avg_wheat = data['wheat'].mean()
    avg_wages = data['wages'].mean()

    sns.barplot(x=['Wheat', 'Wages'], y=[avg_wheat, avg_wages])
    plt.axhline(avg_wheat, color='blue', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Wheat: {avg_wheat:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(avg_wages, color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Wages: {avg_wages:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages over the entire time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
